Generic single-database configuration with async support.

This Alembic environment is configured to work with both Supabase and
PostgreSQL databases. It automatically reads the database URL from your
.env file through the application settings.

## Usage

### Create a new migration
```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description of changes"
```

### Apply migrations
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Rollback one migration
```bash
alembic downgrade -1
```

### View migration history
```bash
alembic history
```

### View current revision
```bash
alembic current
```

## Environment Files

Make sure to use the correct environment file:

### Development (Supabase)
```bash
# Set environment variable before running alembic
set DATABASE_PROVIDER=supabase  # Windows
export DATABASE_PROVIDER=supabase  # Linux/Mac

alembic upgrade head
```

### Production (PostgreSQL)
```bash
# Set environment variable before running alembic
set DATABASE_PROVIDER=postgresql  # Windows
export DATABASE_PROVIDER=postgresql  # Linux/Mac

alembic upgrade head
```

Or use environment files:
```bash
# Load .env.development
python -c "from dotenv import load_dotenv; load_dotenv('.env.development')" && alembic upgrade head

# Load .env.production
python -c "from dotenv import load_dotenv; load_dotenv('.env.production')" && alembic upgrade head
```
